RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 88. Claiming Purse 18500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 2 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 MN Bred Claiming Price $30,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOEL'S ANGEL was sent to an early lead, opened up while racing in the two path around the turn and held his margin to the wire. KING OF THE KIDS trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground steadily in the lane while drifting late. MONGOLIAN BEE raced off the pace early, saved ground around the bend and improved position in the stretch. SHUT UP MICHAEL (IRE) stalked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and was outkicked in the stretch. OUR VALLEY chased the leader on the inside through the opening quarter, saved ground around the turn and faded in the lane. LAPIS LAZULI raced in the middle of the pack up the backstretch, came around the bend in the three path and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 75. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANN ALEE led the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and drew off in the stretch. STRABELLA tracked the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and kept on in the lane, no match for the winner. I'M SO FUNNY chased the leader on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, raced in the two path around the turn and finished evenly, no match for the winner. DROPPED COLD trailed the field throughout, saved ground around the turn and was outrun.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 7 1/2F Turf CR: 95. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 (MINNESOTA BRED $7,500) OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 2 Allowed 2 lbs. Claimi ng Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races fort hree-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOUNTAIN PINE angled over to save ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and dug in in the lane to just hold the win. SUPER WISE raced in the two path early, pressed the pace between horses up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the the three path and gained ground late to the wire to just miss. NOBLE PURSUIT stalked the pace setters on the inside through the opening half mile, continued to save ground around the second turn and gained ground late on the rail to narrowly miss. OF GOOD REPORT raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path and improved position in late stretch. WAR CHEST tracked the leader on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the four path and was outkicked in the lane while finishing evenly. KING NATE raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, came around the second turn in the four path and showed no kick. NACHO S trailed the field the entire way around the oval, saved ground throughout and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 92. Allowance Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FURY KAP raced in the three path around the first turn, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, shook clear while saving ground around the far turn and drew off in the lane while drifting in late. LINE TO GAIN raced off the pace in the two path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the turn, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. CALZONE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the two path, launched a bid approaching the quarter pole and improved position from there. COUSVINNYSACANUCK raced at the back of the pack in the three path through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn in the four path and improved position in the lane. BARNFIELD saved ground around the first turn, raced off the pace up the backstretch, swung out to the four path for the run around the far bend and passed tiring horses in the stretch. DON'T BOX ME IN saved ground early, stalked the leader off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the two path and was outkicked in the lane. GHOST STALKER saved ground around the first bend, trailed the field on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the far turn and never threatened. MOON CONNECTION raced in the three path early, tracked the leader off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the three path and faded from there. MARTINI BLU dueled from the rail around the first turn and up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the two path around the second bend and continued to tire in the stretch. SPIRIT OF SPOATIE raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the second turn and was empty in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEW DICE chased the leader up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn and pulled clear late. INCREDIBLE BILL dueled on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued to battle from the two path coming around the turn, kicked clear in upper stretch and was caught late. GRUNDER raced off the pace between horses early, navigated the bend from the two path and improved position mildly in the lane. STAR OF STARS pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the turn and weakened in the stretch. RISKY SITUATION raced off the pace on the inside through the opening stages, saved ground around the bend and showed no kick. VLOCK raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 61. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MN-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELLE'S LIL DIVA dueled on the inside up the backstretch, led the way while saving ground around the turn and dug in gamely in the stretch to just hold the win. GHOST OF GENEVIEVE dueled on the outside through the opening quarter, dropped back to chase the leader from the two path around the turn, came on again in the lane and dueled to the wire to just miss, the best of the rest. BALIMOS trailed the field early, raced in the two path around the bend and improved position in the lane while never threatening the top two. GIVE EM SHADE tracked the pace setters on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and weakened in the lane. PICAFLOR raced off the pace on the outside through the opening stages, came around the bend in the three path and made no bid. JOMAMA SASSY stalked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and faded in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 7 7 1/2F Turf CR: 62. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-y ear-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUMMER FIREFLYS bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path nearing the quarter pole, gained ground and pulled clear. GRACE A'LACE dueled on the inside through the opening half mile, continued to battle from the two path around the far bend, was caught in the final furlong and kept on to the finish. DIGGS WON bumped with the horse to his inside and was away slowly, saved ground around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. IT'S ME hopped up mildly leaving the gate, saved ground in the middle of the pack around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend and flattened out in the lane. HONEYCRISP raced in the two path around the first bend, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path around the second turn and in upper stretch and weakened in the final furlong. NORTHERN CHARMER raced in the three path early, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn still in the three path and faded from there. O. D.'S ANN BABY raced off the pace in the two path through the opening half mile, continued around the far bend still in the two path and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEAR OLDS, 119 LBS.; OLDER, 124 LBS. Claiming Price $5,000 MN Bred Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOT A DANCE tracked the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, switched to the outside to began a bid in upper stretch and kicked clear late. TAP THAT DIAL dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path around the turn and in upper stretch and was caught in the final strides. WESTERN CHARM bumped with the horse to his outside at the start, recovered to duel on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the bend and was caught late. HE'S CONNECTED raced in the middle of the pack early, came around the turn in the three path, switched to the inside in upper stretch and improved position from there. JAMAICA MISTAICA bumped extensively with the horses to both sides leaving the gate, recovered to stalk the pace setter through the opening quarter, came around the bend in the two path and was outkicked in the lane. CHARISMO raced off the pace up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and showed no kick. FURLOUGH FIT raced at the back of the pack through the opening stages, came around the turn in the three path and was empty in the stretch. FALCONITE bumped with the horse to his inside at the break, dropped back to trail far behind the field racing up the backstretch and never factored.
